==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Buxine
<hw>Bux"ine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid obtained from the <spn>Buxus sempervirens</spn>, or
common box tree. It is identical with <altname>bebeerine</altname>; --
called also <altname>buxina</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buxom</ent>⟦br⟧
